{"body": ">That's not it at all. We have the one of the authors of the HTTP 1.1 spec, and the inventor of REST (which rails at least tries to adhere to...) saying that PUT means only full representations, and that rails is not in line with the HTTP or REST to allow it any other way.\r\n\r\nRoy is an insanely smart guy and definitely an authoritative source on HTTP. His insight and opinion is important. But his opinion does not magically make 2616 more clear on this issue than it is. It's not clear. This is why Roy himself has revised it.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3205125", "created_at": "2011-12-19T16:08:58Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/505#issuecomment-3205125", "updated_at": "2011-12-19T16:08:58Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 505, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/mikekelly", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/fddf4e0508e0ab09171063fc13062b85?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F425fbd8cd12d7ed14264bdd50d8da0b1.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/received_events", "gravatar_id": "fddf4e0508e0ab09171063fc13062b85", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "mikekelly", "type": "User", "id": 55782, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mikekelly/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52385f14bd3543c151012161"}, "id": 3205125, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/505"}
